# Time-related columns

df['Year'] = df['Date_utc'].dt.year
df['Month'] = df['Date_utc'].dt.month
df['Day'] = df['Date_utc'].dt.day
df['Hour'] = df['Date_utc'].dt.hour

def to_local_hour(row):
    if row['Launch_site'] == "CCSFS SLC 40" or row['Launch_site'] == "KSC LC 39A":
        return (row['Hour'] - 4) % 24
    elif row['Launch_site'] == "VAFB SLC 4E":
        return (row['Hour'] - 7) % 24
    else:
        return row['Hour']

df['Local_hour'] = df.apply(to_local_hour, axis=1)

df.drop(['Date_utc', 'Date_utc_unix', 'date_utc_unix', 'date_utc', 'date_local',
    'rocket', 'Orbit', 'Launch_site', 'Landing_type_clean', 'landpad'], axis=1,
    inplace=True)

df = df[cols_order]

def get_smote(features, labels):
    """ Get oversampled data using SMOTE
    """
    smote = SMOTE(sampling_strategy=0.8, k_neighbors=1, random_state=42)
    X_smote, y_smote = smote.fit_resample(features, labels)
    return X_smote, y_smote


def get_preds_cv(model, features, labels):
    """ Get predictions under cross-validation
    """
    X_smote, y_smote = get_smote(features, labels)
    kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    y_preds = cross_val_predict(model, X_smote, y_smote, cv=kf, n_jobs=-1)
    return y_preds


def get_metrics(model, features, labels, show=True):
    """ Get metrics of predictions under cross-validations for binary
        classification
    """
    X_smote, y_smote = get_smote(features, labels)
    y_preds = get_preds_cv(model, features, labels)
    kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    precisions = precision_score(y_smote, y_preds, average=None)
    recalls = recall_score(y_smote, y_preds, average=None)
    f1s = f1_score(y_smote, y_preds, average=None)
    prcs_0, prcs_1 = precisions[0], precisions[1]
    recl_0, recl_1 = recalls[0], recalls[1]
    f1_0, f1_1 = f1s[0], f1s[1]
    acc = accuracy_score(y_smote, y_preds)
    prob_preds = cross_val_predict(model, X_smote, y_smote, cv=kf,
        method='predict_proba')
    logloss = log_loss(y_smote, prob_preds)

    prob_positive_class = prob_preds[:, 1]

    if show:
        print(f"Accuracy {acc:.4f}, Logloss {logloss:.4f}; "
            + f"Class 0: Precision {prcs_0:.4f}, Recall {recl_0:.4f}, f1 {f1_0:.4f}; "
            + f"Class 1: Precision {prcs_1:.4f}, Recall {recl_1:.4f}, f1 {f1_1:.4f}.")
        return {"Accuracy": acc, "Logloss": logloss,
                "Precision cl 0": prcs_0, "Recall cl 0": recl_0, "f1 cl 0": f1_0,
                "Precision cl 1": prcs_1, "Recall cl 1": recl_1, "f1 cl 1": f1_1}
    else:
        return prob_positive_class


def plot_roc(model, features, labels):
    """ Compute and plot the ROC curve
    """
    _, y_smote = get_smote(features, labels)
    prob_positive_class = get_metrics(model, features, labels, show=False)
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_smote, prob_positive_class)
    roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)

    plt.figure(figsize=(4, 3))
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, color='darkorange', lw=2, label='ROC (AUC = %0.2f)' % roc_auc)
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='navy', lw=2, linestyle='--')
    plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
    plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc="lower right")
    plt.show()


def plot_features_imp(model, X_smote, y_smote, kf):
    """ Compute and plot feature importances under cross-validation
    """
    feature_importance_folds = np.zeros((X_smote.shape[1],))

    # Collect feature importances iterating through each fold
    for train_index, _ in kf.split(X_smote):
        X_train, y_train = X_smote.iloc[train_index], y_smote.iloc[train_index]
        model.fit(X_train, y_train)
        feature_importance_folds += model.feature_importances_

    # Average feature importances across all folds
    feature_importance_folds /= kf.get_n_splits()

    sorted_indices = np.argsort(feature_importance_folds)[::-1]
    top_ten_indices = sorted_indices[:10]
    sorted_importances = feature_importance_folds[top_ten_indices]
    sorted_features = X_smote.columns[top_ten_indices]

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 12))
    # plt.bar(range(len(sorted_importances)), sorted_importances)
    # plt.xticks(range(len(sorted_importances)), sorted_features, rotation=270)
    bars = plt.bar(range(len(sorted_importances)), sorted_importances, tick_label=sorted_features)
    for bar, label in zip(bars, sorted_features):
        height = bar.get_height()
        plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, 0, label,
            ha='center', va='bottom', rotation=90, fontsize=20, color='orange', weight='bold')

    # plt.xlabel('Feature')
    plt.ylabel('Feature Importance')
    plt.xticks([])
    plt.yticks(fontsize=16)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


def plot_pmt_imp(model, X_smote, y_smote, kf):
    """ Calculate and plot the permutation importances under cross-validation
    """
    fold_importances = []

    for train_index, test_index in kf.split(X_smote):
        X_train, X_test = X_smote.iloc[train_index], X_smote.iloc[test_index]
        y_train, y_test = y_smote.iloc[train_index], y_smote.iloc[test_index]

        model.fit(X_train, y_train)
        result = permutation_importance(model, X_test, y_test, n_repeats=5,
            random_state=42, n_jobs=-1)
        fold_importances.append(result.importances_mean)

    average_importances = np.mean(fold_importances, axis=0)
    importance_df = pd.DataFrame(average_importances, index=X_smote.columns,
        columns=['Importance']).sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)
    top_ten = importance_df.head(10)

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 12))
    # plt.bar(top_ten.index, top_ten['Importance'])
    bars = plt.bar(range(len(top_ten)), top_ten['Importance'], tick_label=top_ten.index)
    for bar, label in zip(bars, importance_df.index):
        height = bar.get_height()
        plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, 0, label,
            ha='center', va='bottom', rotation=90, fontsize=20, color='orange', weight='bold')

    # plt.xlabel('Features')
    plt.ylabel('Permutation Importance')
    plt.xticks([])
    plt.yticks(fontsize=16)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # return top_ten


def get_tuned_results(features, labels, params, model):
    """ Fine-tune and get the results of a model
    """
    # Define the cross-validation scheme
    kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    X_smote, y_smote = get_smote(features, labels)

    # Fit RandomizedSearchCV to data
    search = RandomizedSearchCV(model(random_state=42), params, n_iter=50, cv=kf,
        verbose=1, scoring='accuracy', random_state=42, n_jobs=-1)
    search.fit(X_smote, y_smote)

    best_params = search.best_params_ # best_score_
    best_model = model(**best_params, random_state=42)
    best_metrics = get_metrics(best_model, features, labels)
    plot_roc(best_model, features, labels)
    plot_features_imp(best_model, X_smote, y_smote, kf)
    plot_pmt_imp(best_model, X_smote, y_smote, kf)

    return best_params, best_metrics

np.random.seed(100)

X_df1 = df1.iloc[:, 1:]
y_df1 = df1.iloc[:, 0]
X_df1[std_cols] = scaler.fit_transform(X_df1[std_cols])
smote = SMOTE(sampling_strategy=0.8, k_neighbors=1, random_state=42)
X_df1, y_df1 = smote.fit_resample(X_df1, y_df1)

# Step 1: Sample a fraction of rows to modify
fraction_to_modify = 0.3  # e.g., modify 30% of rows
num_rows_to_modify = int(len(X_df1) * fraction_to_modify)
rows_to_modify = np.random.choice(X_df1.index, size=num_rows_to_modify, replace=False)

# Step 2: Select a subset of columns to keep for the reduced dataset
num_features = X_df1.shape[1]
num_features_to_keep = int(num_features // 1.5)  # Keep about half the features
features_to_keep = np.random.choice(X_df1.columns, size=num_features_to_keep, replace=False)

# Create the reduced dataset
X_df2 = X_df1.loc[rows_to_modify, features_to_keep].reset_index(drop=True)
y_df2 = y_df1.loc[rows_to_modify].reset_index(drop=True)

# Adjust X_df1 to only have the full-feature rows
X_df1 = X_df1.drop(rows_to_modify).reset_index(drop=True)
